OL,6,F"I also have a duty to the wider
OL,7,Fpublic. I must ensure that you are
OL,8,Fonly released back to society if and
OL,9,Fwhen there is no risk to anyone else,
OL,10,Fthat day, of course, may never come."
OL,12,F"I can not end without mentioning
OL,13,FAlexander. His brief life was one of
OL,14,Fbravery, battling health issues. It
OL,15,Fwas a life filled with love given and
OL,16,Freceived, and for those who knew him,
OL,17,Fhe will never be forgotten, and they
OL,18,Fwill never stop loving him."
